I used CompositedTransformTarget, CompositedTransformFollower, 
and LayerLink to position a dropdown menu precisely above the center of a split button in my UI. 
This ensured the overlay stayed aligned even during layout changes, scrolling, or screen resizing.

The Core Idea
These three work together to:
Attach one widget to another widget’s position — even if they are in different parts of the widget tree (like inside an Overlay).
Think:
Target → “Here is my position.”
Follower → “Stick to that position.”
LayerLink → “Connection wire between them.”


How It Works (Simple Concept)
CompositedTransformTarget marks the widget whose position should be tracked.
LayerLink connects the target and follower.
CompositedTransformFollower, typically inside an Overlay, attaches a floating widget to follow the target’s position.
This setup lets the follower update its transform automatically based on the target’s position at render time.

When Should You Use This?
Use it when:
Building custom dropdown
Building autocomplete
Showing popup below a TextField
Floating menu attached to icon
Tooltip that must track scrolling

🚨 Common Mistakes
Creating different LayerLink objects
→ Must use the same instance.
Not inserting follower inside Overlay
→ It works best when used in Overlay.
Forgetting showWhenUnlinked: false
→ Prevents weird rendering when target disappears.

🧩 Simple Mental Model
LayerLink = Wire
Target    = Leader
Follower  = Follows leader position

=====================================

final LayerLink _link = LayerLink();

OverlayEntry? _overlayEntry;

void _showDropdown() {
  _overlayEntry = OverlayEntry(
    builder: (context) => Positioned(
      width: 200,
      child: CompositedTransformFollower(
        link: _link,
        offset: const Offset(0, 40),
        showWhenUnlinked: false,
        child: Material(
          elevation: 4,
          child: Container(
            height: 150,
            color: Colors.white,
          ),
        ),
      ),
    ),
  );

  Overlay.of(context).insert(_overlayEntry!);
}

In your widget 
CompositedTransformTarget(
  link: _link,
  child: ElevatedButton(
    onPressed: _showDropdown,
    child: Text("Open"),
  ),
)

// Where you want to show the drop down
CompositedTransformFollower(
  link: _layerLink,
  offset: Offset(0, 50),
  child: YourDropdown(),
)
